[While there are a total of 7 more cases reported since the last Global Polio Eradication Initiative update was published (16 Apr 2014), there had been 4 cases reported from Afghanistan in the last post, one of which has been removed from the count; so in fact, there have been 8 newly confirmed cases in this interval -- 7 of them in Pakistan and one in Nigeria. The reports on the vaccination responses in Central Africa are disconcerting as results have been suboptimal for interruption of transmission of the WPV.

For a map of the locations of WPV associated polio cases, see http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek/Poliocasesworldwide.aspx. - Mod.MPP]
